      "id": "PopularPost342632",
      "post_content": "You think [Searing Spear](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Searing Spear) / [Lightning Strike](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Strike) isn't strong enough? Even [Volcanic Hammer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Volcanic Hammer) saw plenty of play. Three (unconditional) damage for two mana *is* the perfect place.  \n  \nYou see, we just scaled back from a ridiculous power creep for a few years. First there was [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), then then came [Goblin Guide](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Guide), [Steppe Lynx](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Steppe Lynx) and [Searing Blaze](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Searing Blaze), and to match that kind of speed, we had [Path to Exile](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile), [Jace, the Mind Sculptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor) and [Bloodbraid Elf](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bloodbraid Elf), and you simply can't keep up with stuff like these without the game becoming degenerate. Return to Ravnica was the first block where Standard started to feel a bit more balanced. [Rakdos Cackler](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rakdos Cackler) is strong but [Voice of Resurgence](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Voice of Resurgence) and [Boros Reckoner](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Reckoner) stop it, which in turn are overpower... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "sweetgab",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost342632\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">You think <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Searing Spear\">Searing Spear</a> / <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Strike\">Lightning Strike</a> isn't strong enough? Even <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Volcanic Hammer\">Volcanic Hammer</a> saw plenty of play. Three (unconditional) damage for two mana <i>is</i> the perfect place.<br/><br/>You see, we just scaled back from a ridiculous power creep for a few years. First there was <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a>, then then came <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Guide\">Goblin Guide</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Steppe Lynx\">Steppe Lynx</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Searing Blaze\">Searing Blaze</a>, and to match that kind of speed, we had <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile\">Path to Exile</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor\">Jace, the Mind Sculptor</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bloodbraid Elf\">Bloodbraid Elf</a>, and you simply can't keep up with stuff like these without the game becoming degenerate. Return to Ravnica was the first block where Standard started to feel a bit more balanced. <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rakdos Cackler\">Rakdos Cackler</a> is strong but <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Voice of Resurgence\">Voice of Resurgence</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Reckoner\">Boros Reckoner</a> stop it, which in turn are overpower... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick